     To demonstrate current induced switching of magnetism in FGaT, we have fabricated bilayer devices of exfoliated FGaT flakes (bottom) and 6 nm sputtered Pt (top). The bilayer stack is patterned into a Hall bar device and anomalous Hall resistance measurements are used to track the magnetization state of FGaT in the switching experiments. Figure

      2e

     shows the optical image of one such device, D1, with 57.9 nm FGaT and 6 nm Pt patterned into a 5




